knowledge_graph.title: Junket
knowledge_graph.description: Junket is a milk-based dessert with a jelly texture, made with sweetened milk and rennet, the digestive enzyme that curdles milk. It is usually set in a mould and served cold. Some similar desserts are Ostkaka, Blancmange, panna cotta, Tavuk göğsü, almond tofu, haupia and tembleque.

related_questions.question: Is junket still made?
related_questions.snippet: Rennet tablets, commonly referred to as "Junket tablets", are a common source of rennet for home cheesemakers. The "Junket" brand is now owned and operated by Junket Foods LLC a St. Louis Missouri company with a history with ice cream.

related_questions.question: What is a junket in business?
related_questions.snippet: (dʒʌŋkɪt ) Word forms: junkets. countable noun. If you describe a trip or visit by an official or businessperson as a junket, you disapprove of it because it is expensive, unnecessary, and often has been paid for with public money.

definitions: an extravagant trip or celebration, in particular one enjoyed by a government official at public expense.
a dish of sweetened and flavored curds of milk, often served with fruit.
attend or go on a trip or celebration at public expense.
examples: the latest row over city council junkets
the mayor junketed off to Christchurch for a cricket match last week

buttons.snippet: What is Junket? Junket is an old English dessert made with creamy milk, sugar and other flavourings like nutmeg. The milk is curdled with rennet (rennin enzyme), which gives it a soft, creamy pudding like texture. If you were trying to compare it with something, it's a lot like a set milk jelly.
